title: Nunburnholme railway station
data: Nunburnholme railway station was a railway station on the York to Beverley Line in the East Riding of Yorkshire, England. It opened in 1848 as Burnby, and was renamed 1873. It closed in 1951. Burnby railway station opened in 1848. It was renamed Nunburnholme on 1 January 1873.[1] The station served the villages of Nunburnholme and Burnby. It closed on 31 March 1951.[1] This article on a railway station in Yorkshire and the Humber is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.
